D.9 verify (2026-05-13):

D.9 = LP-mapping acceptance E2E. kind: verify-only (no plan-step code
changes BUT this step did surface 5 real bugs that were fixed inline).

Bugs caught + fixed during D.9:
  1. Worker dispatcher Lambda was stripping `inputs` from the pool NOTIFY
     payload — agent never saw RunInputs. Fix in worker/dispatcher/handler.ts:
     forward inputs/automationId/automationVersion/triggeredBy.
  2. Worker main.ts ignored msg.inputs in the prompt. Fix:
     renderInputsBlock prepends a structured JSON block to goal so the
     agent reads RunInputs verbatim.
  3. automation-trigger-registry.ts loadConnectedAccountByToolkit used
     workspace_id as Composio user_id, but the workspace's connected
     accounts live under account_id (matching worker/src/composio/
     connection-resolver.ts). Fix: take optional composioUserId param,
     filter to ACTIVE status only.
  4. cron-kicker `cloud_agents.settings` column reference was wrong (the
     column is `composio_user_id`). Fix in automation-trigger-registry.
  5. Composio webhook signature mismatch: COMPOSIO_WEBHOOK_SECRET in our
     env did not match Composio dashboard. Pulled the real secret via
     /api/v3/webhook_subscriptions/{id}, set via sst secret, redeployed.

In-step feature added (per operator request):
  Per-automation approval-rule remember. Migration 0024 added
  automation_id column to approval_rules. C.3 lookupApprovalRule extended
  with currentAutomationId param. WorkerToolContext.automationId set by
  opencode-plugin via JOIN cloud_session_bindings + cloud_runs. POST
  /v1/approvals/:id remember=true now also works on signed-token path
  (using run owner as created_by) and scopes by automation_id. Sendblue
  inbound webhook parseReply expanded with REMEMBER_APPROVE_LEXICON
  ('ya', 'y!', 'yes always', 'always', 'remember', 'allow always', ...).
  Auto-expire: PUT /v1/automations/:id DELETEs all rules for that
  automation_id (any edit invalidates the standing pattern). Rule
  pattern strips B.5 "<redacted>" fields before INSERT so JSONB
  containment matches live unscrubbed args.

